Availability: Docs
Title:Global Illumination
Crumbs:%ROOT%, Resources, Resources/Showcases/PostProcessing
Description:A rundown of how Global Illumination was employed within the Post Process Matinee example included with UE4.


The Global Illumination settings allow you to enhance and modify the light bounced throughout the scene via Lightmass. This gives you the power to tweak bounced light without having to adjust lights or rebuild.

![](GISettings.png)

| **Property** | **Use in this scene** | **Before/After** |
|---|---|:---:|
| **Indirect Lighting Color** | This is a tint applied to the color of all bounced light. In this scene, it is used to add a significant cooling factor to the lights. | [INCLUDE:#IndirectColor] |
| **Indirect Lighting Intensity** | This is used to boost the amount of bounced light tenfold, giving a brighter sense of overall global illumination. | [INCLUDE:#AO] |







